### Item 6: Widget Registry Optimization (P2)

**Status:** 🔲 PLANNING REQUIRED

**Problem Statement:**
Dashboard.tsx has 45+ individual lazy imports:
```typescript
const QuoteWidget = lazy(() => import('../widgets/Dashboard/QuoteWidget').then(m => ({ default: m.QuoteWidget })));
// Repeated 45+ times
```

**Goal:** Centralized registry with dynamic loading and better code splitting.

**Architecture:**

```typescript
// src/widgets/Dashboard/registry.ts
export interface WidgetDefinition {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  category: WidgetCategory;
  component: LazyExoticComponent<ComponentType<WidgetProps>>;
  defaultSize: 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';
  minSize?: { cols: number; rows: number };
  icon: string;
}

// Auto-discovery using Vite glob imports
const widgetModules = import.meta.glob<{ default: ComponentType }>('./*/index.tsx');

export const widgetRegistry: Map<string, WidgetDefinition> = new Map();

// Register all widgets
for (const [path, loader] of Object.entries(widgetModules)) {
  const id = path.match(/\.\/(.+)\/index\.tsx/)?.[1];
  if (id) {
    widgetRegistry.set(id, {
      id,
      component: lazy(loader),
      // ... metadata from widget's config export
    });
  }
}
```

**Implementation Phases:**

**Phase 1: Create Registry Types (1 hour)**
```typescript
// src/widgets/Dashboard/types.ts
export interface WidgetConfig {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  category: WidgetCategory;
  icon: string;
  defaultSize: WidgetSize;
  minSize?: { cols: number; rows: number };
  maxSize?: { cols: number; rows: number };
}
```

**Phase 2: Update Widget Structure (2-3 hours)**
```
widgets/Dashboard/
├── registry.ts           # Central registry
├── types.ts             # Widget types
├── QuoteWidget/
│   ├── index.tsx        # Widget component
│   └── config.ts        # Widget metadata
├── WeatherWidget/
│   ├── index.tsx
│   └── config.ts
└── ...
```

**Phase 3: Implement Registry (2-3 hours)**
- Vite glob imports for auto-discovery
- Lazy loading with error boundaries
- Preloading for visible widgets

**Phase 4: Migrate Dashboard.tsx (2-3 hours)**
```typescript
// Before: 45+ individual imports
const QuoteWidget = lazy(() => ...);

// After: Single registry lookup
const WidgetComponent = widgetRegistry.get(widgetId)?.component;
```

**Phase 5: Chunk Optimization (1-2 hours)**
- Group related widgets into chunks
- Configure Vite manual chunks
- Verify bundle sizes

**Estimated Total:** 8-12 hours

**Success Criteria:**
- [ ] Single registry for all widgets
- [ ] Dashboard.tsx under 200 lines
- [ ] Widget metadata centralized
- [ ] Bundle size unchanged or smaller
- [ ] Load time unchanged or faster

---

### Item 7: Widget Loading/Error State Integration (P2)

**Status:** 🔲 PLANNING REQUIRED

**Problem Statement:**
- `Widget.tsx` (container) has no loading/error states
- `BaseWidget.tsx` (content) has loading/error states
- Inconsistent UX across widgets

**Goal:** Unified loading/error handling for all widgets.

**Architecture:**

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Widget.tsx (Container)                 │
│  - Drag handle, controls, header       │
│  - Error boundary (already added)      │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │  BaseWidget.tsx (Content)        │  │
│  │  - Loading spinner               │  │
│  │  - Error state with retry        │  │
│  │  - Empty state                   │  │
│  │  ┌────────────────────────────┐  │  │
│  │  │  Actual Widget Content     │  │  │
│  │  └────────────────────────────┘  │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────┘  │
└────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Implementation Phases:**

**Phase 1: Enhance BaseWidget (1-2 hours)**
```typescript
export interface BaseWidgetProps {
  // Existing
  title: string;
  icon: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
  loading?: boolean;
  error?: string | null;
  onRefresh?: () => void;

  // New
  isEmpty?: boolean;
  emptyMessage?: string;
  emptyAction?: { label: string; onClick: () => void };
  retryCount?: number;
  maxRetries?: number;
}
```

**Phase 2: Create useWidgetData Hook (2-3 hours)**
```typescript
// src/hooks/useWidgetData.ts
export function useWidgetData<T>(
  fetcher: () => Promise<T>,
  options: {
    refreshInterval?: number;
    retryOnError?: boolean;
    maxRetries?: number;
  } = {}
) {
  const [data, setData] = useState<T | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [retryCount, setRetryCount] = useState(0);

  const refresh = useCallback(async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    try {
      const result = await fetcher();
      setData(result);
    } catch (e) {
      setError(e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Unknown error');
      if (options.retryOnError && retryCount < (options.maxRetries ?? 3)) {
        setRetryCount(c => c + 1);
      }
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }, [fetcher, retryCount, options]);

  return { data, loading, error, refresh, retryCount };
}
```

**Phase 3: Migrate Widgets (4-6 hours)**
```typescript
// Example: WeatherWidget migration
export const WeatherWidget: React.FC = () => {
  const { data, loading, error, refresh } = useWidgetData(
    () => fetchWeather(),
    { refreshInterval: 300000 } // 5 minutes
  );

  return (
    <BaseWidget
      title="Weather"
      icon="🌤️"
      loading={loading}
      error={error}
      onRefresh={refresh}
      isEmpty={!data}
      emptyMessage="No weather data available"
    >
      {data && <WeatherDisplay data={data} />}
    </BaseWidget>
  );
};
```

**Estimated Total:** 7-11 hours

**Success Criteria:**
- [ ] All widgets have loading states
- [ ] All widgets have error states with retry
- [ ] Empty states are handled consistently
- [ ] useWidgetData hook documented
- [ ] No widget crashes break the dashboard

---

## Execution Order

**Recommended sequence:**

1. **Simple Items** (ongoing, parallel)
   - Console log cleanup (2-3 files/session)
   - CSS tokens audit (1 session)
   - Documentation (as needed)

2. **Test Infrastructure** (P1, do first)
   - Enables validation of other changes
   - 8-12 hours

3. **Widget Loading/Error Integration** (P2)
   - Lower risk, immediate UX benefit
   - 7-11 hours

4. **Widget Registry Optimization** (P2)
   - Depends on widget error integration
   - 8-12 hours

5. **Unified State Persistence** (P1, do last)
   - Highest risk, most impact
   - Needs thorough testing
   - 10-14 hours

**Total Estimated Time:** 33-49 hours (spread over multiple sessions)

